+# Doughnut Recall Forecast Counts
+
+## User Story
+
+As a learner, I want the Recall page to show how many recall items are due now and how many more would be loaded from the next 3, 7, and 14 days, so that I can decide whether to continue recalling without blindly clicking each load-more button.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- The recall API exposes forecast counts for due windows 0, 3, 7, and 14 days.
+- Forecast windows use the same learner timezone and half-day recall alignment rules as existing recall loading.
+- Forecast counts are monotonic by window: 0 <= 3 <= 7 <= 14.
+- Forecast counts exclude deleted notes and removed memory trackers.
+- Existing load-more behavior for next 3, 7, and 14 days remains compatible.
+- The Recall page done state and load-more buttons show the relevant forecast counts.
+- Treadmill mode and existing current-session progress remain unchanged.
+- Backend and frontend tests cover the practical behavior surface.
+
+## Non-Goals
+
+- Rewriting recall flow, spaced repetition scoring, or treadmill behavior.
+- Changing generated benchmark artifacts outside this repository worktree.
+- Introducing unrelated schema or API changes.
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+- API callers can retrieve current and future recall counts for the configured windows.
+- UI presents the forecast where learners choose whether to load additional items.
+- Targeted backend validation passes for recall service behavior.
+
